  "text": "And then, as in our previous study, [CITATION_1] the position of the 3D model was adjusted carefully to find the largest screw path (translucent area that could accommodate a screw with largest diameter). The image with the largest translucent area showing in the computer was the simulation of the anterior column axial view projection (Figure 1 ), which would be helpful in identifying and confirming the anterior column axial view image obtained intraoperatively.",
